# Experimental query compilation JIT

## Description

Just-in-time compilation of queries to native code.

## Implementation

```rust
pub fn query_compilation_jit() {
    // Generate LLVM IR from query plan
    // Compile to native code
    // Execute compiled pipeline
}
```

## Cost Model

- Compilation: 10-100ms one-time cost
- Execution: 5-10x faster than interpretation
- Break-even: ~1000 rows processed

## References

1. Neumann, "Efficiently Compiling Efficient Query Plans for Modern Hardware", VLDB 2011
2. Shaikhha et al., "How to Architect a Query Compiler, Revisited", SIGMOD 2018
